WEBVTT

00:00:38.722 --> 00:00:40.188
What exactly...

00:00:40.188 --> 00:00:43.435
is going on right now?

00:00:43.435 --> 00:00:45.695
Well...

00:00:53.605 --> 00:00:55.564
It just looks like...

00:00:55.564 --> 00:00:57.616
two people who were into each other

00:00:57.616 --> 00:01:00.334
ended up spending the night together...

00:01:01.731 --> 00:01:04.208
But I can't explain why he's here with us.

00:01:04.208 --> 00:01:07.647
Oh, I stepped outside for a little fresh air.

00:01:07.647 --> 00:01:08.788
Oh, yeah!

00:01:08.788 --> 00:01:10.045
In front of that cafe.

00:01:10.045 --> 00:01:13.048
We were talking about hitting up
another spot there... weren't we?

00:01:13.048 --> 00:01:14.221
What is this, a mystery game?

00:01:14.221 --> 00:01:17.768
Trying to patch up a bunch of blank spots
isn't going to get you anywhere.

00:01:25.644 --> 00:01:26.962
Watch it.

00:01:26.962 --> 00:01:31.097
Tae Seop. One, two. One, two.

00:01:31.097 --> 00:01:32.984
We're almost there.

00:01:32.984 --> 00:01:35.009
Hold on.

00:01:36.439 --> 00:01:38.731
God, this is driving me crazy.

00:01:38.731 --> 00:01:40.314
Maybe I should just ditch him.

00:01:40.314 --> 00:01:42.355
Please don't go without me.

00:01:42.355 --> 00:01:45.289
It's not like he's some clingy little dog...

00:01:45.289 --> 00:01:47.757
One, two, three!

00:01:50.135 --> 00:01:51.169
Hey, Lee Ui Yeong.

00:01:51.169 --> 00:01:52.871
Oh, Shin Ji Su.

00:01:52.871 --> 00:01:55.465
What are you doing here?
Aren't you supposed to be at the cafe?

00:01:55.465 --> 00:01:56.711
Wait, I have no idea.

00:01:56.711 --> 00:01:59.386
I forgot something back at the hotel.

00:01:59.386 --> 00:02:01.331
Hey, how come you're passed out
on her shoulder?

00:02:01.331 --> 00:02:03.522
- Hey!
- I'm taking him to the hotel.

00:02:03.522 --> 00:02:06.031
Wait, you two are going to a hotel like this?

00:02:06.031 --> 00:02:07.171
- Let's go.
- What?

00:02:07.171 --> 00:02:09.542
Come on, unless you'd rather
sleep out here on the street.

00:02:09.542 --> 00:02:11.439
- Give me a sec.
- Jeez.

00:02:11.439 --> 00:02:13.199
Let's go.

00:02:34.105 --> 00:02:35.522
Water...

00:02:35.522 --> 00:02:38.897
Can I get some water, please?

00:02:38.897 --> 00:02:41.060
Oh, come on.

00:02:54.188 --> 00:02:55.825
Here.

00:03:13.410 --> 00:03:15.522
- That's cold.
- Oh, seriously.

00:03:15.522 --> 00:03:17.064
This guy just keeps surprising me.

00:03:17.064 --> 00:03:19.265
It's cold.

00:03:29.105 --> 00:03:31.235
Ui Yeong, let's go.

00:03:35.064 --> 00:03:36.907
You asleep?

00:03:37.981 --> 00:03:39.910
These two together...

00:03:40.522 --> 00:03:42.371
No.

00:04:10.230 --> 00:04:12.526
It hurts.

00:04:36.918 --> 00:04:39.136
She turns into a whole different person
when she drinks.

00:05:06.948 --> 00:05:08.897
There's no way I'm leaving

00:05:08.897 --> 00:05:10.835
the two of them by themselves.

00:06:05.757 --> 00:06:09.261
[Episode 6]

00:06:10.720 --> 00:06:13.279
I'm sorry.
You couldn't even go home because of me.

00:06:13.279 --> 00:06:14.739
No, it's fine. I'm okay.

00:06:14.739 --> 00:06:16.118
Fine, my ass.

00:06:16.118 --> 00:06:19.419
Who just walks into a hotel
with some random guy...

00:06:19.419 --> 00:06:20.879
If I hadn't shown up, then what?

00:06:20.879 --> 00:06:23.314
Hey, I know I owe you one,

00:06:23.314 --> 00:06:24.776
but even if I'm a total lightweight,

00:06:24.776 --> 00:06:27.738
it doesn't make me some kind of creep.

00:06:27.738 --> 00:06:31.449
You can't even tell how much you drink,
so how can you judge how you act?

00:06:31.449 --> 00:06:33.159
What is this, summer camp?

00:06:33.159 --> 00:06:34.731
Summer camp?

00:06:34.731 --> 00:06:35.996
That's enough.

00:06:35.996 --> 00:06:37.409
Quit giving him a hard time.

00:06:37.409 --> 00:06:41.008
If nothing went wrong, then just drop it.

00:06:42.877 --> 00:06:44.104
Alright,

00:06:44.104 --> 00:06:47.131
I'd better head out
before the morning shift gets here.

00:06:47.131 --> 00:06:48.525
Why don't you clean up first?

00:06:48.525 --> 00:06:49.606
I mean, you guys spent
the whole night in the same room.

00:06:49.606 --> 00:06:51.136
Hey!

00:06:52.396 --> 00:06:55.515
The employee showers
are actually pretty decent.

00:06:55.515 --> 00:06:56.521
Alright.

00:06:56.521 --> 00:06:58.026
Better get out of here
before it gets complicated.

00:06:58.026 --> 00:06:59.285
Sure.

00:06:59.285 --> 00:07:01.188
Wait.

00:07:01.188 --> 00:07:02.605
Oh, I almost forgot.

00:07:02.605 --> 00:07:03.913
Thank you.

00:07:03.913 --> 00:07:05.566
I'm really embarrassed about all this.

00:07:05.566 --> 00:07:07.874
Could I buy you dinner this weekend
to make it up to you?

00:07:07.874 --> 00:07:10.313
Anything you want, it's on me.

00:07:11.238 --> 00:07:12.433
Sounds good.

00:07:12.433 --> 00:07:15.413
Would Saturday work for you?

00:07:15.413 --> 00:07:17.073
Sure, a meal sounds nice.

00:07:17.073 --> 00:07:20.289
And if you want to thank me,
skip the words and just feed me.

00:07:20.289 --> 00:07:21.894
Your debt to me just keeps piling up.

00:07:21.894 --> 00:07:24.939
I'll treat you. That's what I just said.

00:07:24.939 --> 00:07:27.814
- I'll send you the details by text.
- Got it.

00:07:27.814 --> 00:07:30.021
- Have a good day at work.
- Yeah.

00:07:30.021 --> 00:07:31.772
I'm off.

00:07:31.772 --> 00:07:33.435
Alright.

00:07:38.813 --> 00:07:40.521
I can't believe this, I really can't.

00:07:40.521 --> 00:07:42.061
What if somebody caught that?

00:07:42.061 --> 00:07:44.070
Seriously.

00:08:01.205 --> 00:08:02.964
Wait a minute.

00:08:04.063 --> 00:08:06.259
Isn't it suspiciously peaceful?

00:08:13.050 --> 00:08:16.228
She didn't cause me any trouble
for her entire twenties.

00:08:17.680 --> 00:08:20.391
She's really testing me now.

00:08:20.391 --> 00:08:24.491
I've burned through all my energy
and it's barely morning.

00:08:24.491 --> 00:08:27.280
Maybe I need some coffee.

00:08:28.691 --> 00:08:30.450
What's this?

00:08:32.319 --> 00:08:35.359
[A little pick-me-up just for you, Hyun Min]

00:08:39.563 --> 00:08:42.546
Always so sweet, Jung Hyun Min.

00:09:10.634 --> 00:09:11.650
Lee Ui Yeong.

00:09:11.650 --> 00:09:12.902
Where are you?

00:09:12.902 --> 00:09:14.320
Letting me know ahead of time
if you're staying out

00:09:14.320 --> 00:09:16.865
is common courtesy as a roommate, right?

00:09:16.865 --> 00:09:20.542
No reply by 9 and I'm reporting you missing.

00:09:21.605 --> 00:09:24.121
The project launched
and we went out to celebrate,

00:09:24.121 --> 00:09:26.916
but it went on forever
so I crashed in the rest area.

00:09:26.916 --> 00:09:28.800
I'm sorry.

00:10:06.789 --> 00:10:08.798
You're using my towel.

00:10:12.730 --> 00:10:13.838
So

00:10:13.838 --> 00:10:16.504
you spent the whole night keeping tabs on us?

00:10:16.504 --> 00:10:18.745
Doesn't that seem like it crossed
a line for someone just being nice?

00:10:18.745 --> 00:10:22.479
The one who went too far is you,
passing out drunk on a woman.

00:10:23.389 --> 00:10:25.365
What kind of guy gets knocked out that easily?

00:10:25.365 --> 00:10:27.124
Stop trying to dodge the point.

00:10:27.124 --> 00:10:30.105
I don't like how you keep circling
around Ui Yeong.

00:10:30.105 --> 00:10:32.864
It looks like you're just waiting
for your chance, pretending to care.

00:10:32.864 --> 00:10:35.046
Circling around?

00:10:35.046 --> 00:10:37.146
Someone as hopeless as you

00:10:37.146 --> 00:10:38.966
wouldn't recognize an opening
if it hit you in the face.

00:10:38.966 --> 00:10:40.705
Hopeless?

00:10:56.214 --> 00:10:58.747
Wait, this isn't what you think.
There's a reason for all this.

00:10:58.747 --> 00:11:00.718
I saw nothing.

00:11:00.718 --> 00:11:03.051
I don't need the details of your personal life.

00:11:03.051 --> 00:11:04.305
I really need to clear this up.

00:11:04.305 --> 00:11:05.577
Manager. Wait, please.

00:11:05.577 --> 00:11:07.980
This is all a big mix-up.

00:11:07.980 --> 00:11:09.776
Oh, for crying out loud.

00:11:15.355 --> 00:11:19.596
Nothing stays private in this hotel.

00:11:19.596 --> 00:11:21.396
The employees who spotted them are saying

00:11:21.396 --> 00:11:25.827
it wasn't just one man, it was actually two.

00:11:25.827 --> 00:11:28.392
That kind of lets me down, if I'm being real.

00:11:28.392 --> 00:11:29.397
How come?

00:11:29.397 --> 00:11:31.583
Dating more than one person at once

00:11:31.583 --> 00:11:32.959
has nothing to do with love.

00:11:32.959 --> 00:11:36.146
Who says you can't enjoy yourself
and be in love at the same time?

00:11:36.146 --> 00:11:37.897
Think about it, Sae Byeok.

00:11:37.897 --> 00:11:40.837
People these days are so judgmental
and closed off.

00:11:40.837 --> 00:11:43.356
It's all black and white.
If it's not love, it's wrong.

00:11:43.356 --> 00:11:45.262
So everyone ends up doing things
behind closed doors,

00:11:45.262 --> 00:11:49.183
then they get exposed
and it all blows up in their face, right?

00:11:49.183 --> 00:11:50.480
Ui Yeong.

00:11:50.480 --> 00:11:52.533
When did you get here?

00:11:52.533 --> 00:11:55.480
Just now. I just got here.

00:11:55.480 --> 00:11:57.396
Look, though...

00:11:57.396 --> 00:12:00.313
Isn't that going a little too far?

00:12:00.313 --> 00:12:03.954
You don't buy into those gossip rags, do you?

00:12:03.954 --> 00:12:05.157
Sorry?

00:12:05.157 --> 00:12:08.035
Gossip about what?

00:12:08.035 --> 00:12:09.355
Despite being in her 50s,

00:12:09.355 --> 00:12:13.093
Ms. S remains unchallenged
as the reigning Queen of Romance.

00:12:13.093 --> 00:12:15.000
Once said to be married to her craft,

00:12:15.000 --> 00:12:18.423
it turns out she's been wrapped up
in actual romance lately.

00:12:18.423 --> 00:12:19.797
Sources claim she's living

00:12:19.797 --> 00:12:22.271
with surgeon A,
a former affair turned domestic partner,

00:12:22.271 --> 00:12:24.760
while also seeing director B secretly
at a high-end hotel,

00:12:24.760 --> 00:12:26.480
and financially supporting model C
on top of all that.

00:12:26.480 --> 00:12:28.313
Given her extensive list of romantic interests,

00:12:28.313 --> 00:12:31.146
this story is only going to get bigger.

00:12:31.146 --> 00:12:33.313
The Queen of Romance...

00:12:33.313 --> 00:12:35.063
That has to be actress Son Jeong A, right?

00:12:35.063 --> 00:12:37.189
They might as well have just said her name.

00:12:37.189 --> 00:12:39.900
I heard she booked a room
at our hotel not long ago.

00:12:39.900 --> 00:12:41.688
Are you serious?

00:12:41.688 --> 00:12:43.355
That makes our hotel

00:12:43.355 --> 00:12:45.705
the secret meeting spot.

00:12:56.611 --> 00:12:57.647
Hey,

00:12:57.647 --> 00:12:59.521
Director Jin said

00:12:59.521 --> 00:13:01.411
he won't be at today's meeting.

00:13:01.411 --> 00:13:04.241
He just got married and doesn't want
people getting the wrong idea.

00:13:05.651 --> 00:13:07.772
So it's only for today?

00:13:07.772 --> 00:13:09.813
Or is he cutting me from the movie altogether?

00:13:09.813 --> 00:13:11.473
The thing is...

00:13:11.473 --> 00:13:13.597
What a wimp.

00:13:13.597 --> 00:13:14.612
Tell him to forget it.

00:13:14.612 --> 00:13:15.979
Let's just eat and head back.

00:13:15.979 --> 00:13:17.191
Take a seat.

00:13:17.191 --> 00:13:18.696
Okay.

00:13:22.193 --> 00:13:23.235
Excuse me,

00:13:23.235 --> 00:13:25.995
I'm Kim Min Seong from Star E.

00:13:26.682 --> 00:13:29.882
Any reason you've stayed silent
on the tabloid story?

00:13:29.882 --> 00:13:32.822
Speaking too soon would only make things worse.

00:13:32.822 --> 00:13:34.409
A statement's coming shortly.

00:13:34.409 --> 00:13:35.414
However, Mr. Kim,

00:13:35.414 --> 00:13:37.920
this is a private setting, so following me here

00:13:37.920 --> 00:13:39.794
isn't appropriate.

00:13:39.794 --> 00:13:42.589
What? I can't believe you people!

00:13:44.146 --> 00:13:45.922
Dong Hoon!

00:13:45.922 --> 00:13:48.181
Call 119, please.

00:13:48.181 --> 00:13:50.373
Here we have a single larva.

00:13:50.373 --> 00:13:51.430
In its quest to reach maturity,

00:13:51.430 --> 00:13:54.017
if you trace the molted layers it left behind,

00:13:54.017 --> 00:13:55.271
following one last shedding,

00:13:55.271 --> 00:13:56.894
it has burrowed into its duvet chrysalis

00:13:56.894 --> 00:14:00.855
and achieved complete pupal form.

00:14:00.855 --> 00:14:03.401
Stop messing around.

00:14:03.401 --> 00:14:06.661
The chrysalis is at last
undergoing transformation.

00:14:06.661 --> 00:14:09.262
Seriously though,
will I ever feel normal again?

00:14:09.262 --> 00:14:12.647
I think my entire body just shut down.

00:14:12.647 --> 00:14:14.266
Come on, get up already.

00:14:25.542 --> 00:14:27.583
It's not just your first hangover.

00:14:27.583 --> 00:14:29.642
It's your first time recovering from one, too.

00:14:31.386 --> 00:14:34.403
I wouldn't have a word to say
if she never talked to me again.

00:14:34.403 --> 00:14:35.843
This is insane.

00:14:35.843 --> 00:14:38.063
I barely had a chance
to make a good impression,

00:14:38.063 --> 00:14:40.063
and I just had to go drink
more than I could take.

00:14:40.063 --> 00:14:42.082
What's done is done, dude.

00:14:42.082 --> 00:14:44.402
Ui Yeong was wasted too, wasn't she?

00:14:44.402 --> 00:14:47.939
She's most likely
freaking out just as much. Relax.

00:14:47.939 --> 00:14:49.603
What a waste, hey.

00:14:49.603 --> 00:14:50.911
Why aren't

00:14:50.911 --> 00:14:55.501
you eating any of these dishes
your mom put together for you?

00:14:56.120 --> 00:14:58.404
You've got plans with Ui Yeong
this Saturday, don't you?

00:14:58.404 --> 00:15:00.704
That's great.

00:15:00.704 --> 00:15:02.710
Replace the old flame with a fresh face,

00:15:02.710 --> 00:15:04.578
wash down the hangover with a bowl of broth,

00:15:04.578 --> 00:15:07.605
and bury those ugly memories
under brand new ones.

00:15:07.605 --> 00:15:08.966
Gosh,

00:15:08.966 --> 00:15:11.468
this really hits the spot.

00:15:11.468 --> 00:15:13.605
So what's the plan?

00:15:13.605 --> 00:15:14.647
Well...

00:15:14.647 --> 00:15:16.474
I'm thinking a nice dinner with her,

00:15:16.474 --> 00:15:19.352
and we'll catch a movie we haven't seen.

00:15:19.352 --> 00:15:20.825
So everything's already figured out?

00:15:20.825 --> 00:15:23.446
Not even close. I'm only getting started.

00:15:24.688 --> 00:15:26.355
I have to make that whole drunk disaster

00:15:26.355 --> 00:15:28.493
completely disappear from her memory.

00:15:32.447 --> 00:15:34.116
I'm not leaving

00:15:34.116 --> 00:15:37.452
until Son Jeong A shows her face today.

00:15:37.452 --> 00:15:39.104
Can you see?

00:15:39.104 --> 00:15:42.048
Man, the press is swarming out here.

00:15:43.730 --> 00:15:45.718
This is a mess.

00:15:47.563 --> 00:15:49.066
So much for going home.

00:15:49.066 --> 00:15:50.415
[Son Jeong A's mystery lovers, A, B, C]
For those kinds of prices,

00:15:50.415 --> 00:15:52.077
they could keep things private.

00:15:52.077 --> 00:15:54.519
There's just way too many famous people
in that building.

00:15:55.647 --> 00:15:57.355
Given how crazy everything is right now,

00:15:57.355 --> 00:15:59.531
riding around with you in my car
isn't really an option,

00:15:59.531 --> 00:16:02.360
so lay low here for the time being.

00:16:03.438 --> 00:16:05.397
Lately, the strategy is
to lock in your concept,

00:16:05.397 --> 00:16:07.482
put together all your evidence,
and hit them with

00:16:07.482 --> 00:16:11.813
a single well-planned feature piece
that says it all.

00:16:11.813 --> 00:16:13.450
Yeah.

00:16:13.450 --> 00:16:15.271
Sure beats chasing

00:16:15.271 --> 00:16:17.298
after every low-quality hit piece
that comes out.

00:16:17.298 --> 00:16:18.703
It's not like I'm some
twenty- or thirty-something.

00:16:18.703 --> 00:16:20.962
I've got nothing left to lose.

00:16:21.895 --> 00:16:24.813
Look into journalists who can
tell my side properly.

00:16:24.813 --> 00:16:26.480
Covering up a love scandal

00:16:26.480 --> 00:16:29.313
by telling an even greater love story.

00:16:29.313 --> 00:16:30.590
Brilliant, truly brilliant.

00:16:30.590 --> 00:16:31.656
Pardon me,

00:16:31.656 --> 00:16:34.096
the press has zero access
to this area, correct?

00:16:34.096 --> 00:16:36.060
Please don't worry.

00:16:36.730 --> 00:16:38.480
Well then,

00:16:38.480 --> 00:16:39.681
I was wondering...

00:16:39.681 --> 00:16:43.019
are you familiar with what we call GRO?

00:16:43.019 --> 00:16:44.087
No.

00:16:44.087 --> 00:16:45.103
What's that?

00:16:45.103 --> 00:16:47.022
In a nutshell,

00:16:47.022 --> 00:16:50.067
it's like having a dedicated assistant
for everything during your visit.

00:16:50.067 --> 00:16:51.151
While you're with us,

00:16:51.151 --> 00:16:53.438
we could pair you
with a staff member who handles

00:16:53.438 --> 00:16:56.783
your schedule and shopping needs.

00:16:56.783 --> 00:16:58.262
That sounds great!

00:16:58.262 --> 00:17:00.743
Make sure she's a woman with good taste.

00:17:00.743 --> 00:17:03.242
Of course, let me find someone.

00:17:03.242 --> 00:17:04.860
I'll take my leave.

00:17:09.980 --> 00:17:12.063
- Gosh.
- It will work out this time.

00:17:12.063 --> 00:17:13.090
Have you read that piece yet?

00:17:13.090 --> 00:17:15.461
[Final candidate for HKUH Director]

00:17:20.721 --> 00:17:23.558
All day long, every corner I turned,
people were talking about you.

00:17:23.558 --> 00:17:25.121
And look who decided to show up in person.

00:17:25.121 --> 00:17:28.221
Somehow you landed in a tabloid
rather than a research publication.

00:17:28.221 --> 00:17:29.813
Oh, is that so?

00:17:29.813 --> 00:17:32.230
Honestly, even just being vice director

00:17:32.230 --> 00:17:34.361
already seemed too generous,

00:17:34.361 --> 00:17:36.029
but everyone kept pressuring me
to go for director

00:17:36.029 --> 00:17:37.855
because of what it would mean
for the hospital's image,

00:17:37.855 --> 00:17:40.076
and they just wouldn't let up...

00:17:40.076 --> 00:17:42.244
Now it makes sense
why everyone was acting strange,

00:17:42.244 --> 00:17:44.670
so this is what's behind it.

00:17:45.647 --> 00:17:46.772
But

00:17:46.772 --> 00:17:48.855
rumors really do make
for good entertainment, don't they?

00:17:48.855 --> 00:17:52.462
A man of your schedule,
showing up for a little gossip...

00:17:52.462 --> 00:17:54.313
Standing in the corridor
gushing like schoolchildren.

00:17:54.313 --> 00:17:57.053
Judging by how thrilled you look,

00:17:57.053 --> 00:17:59.477
it must be quite the topic.

00:18:00.730 --> 00:18:03.481
I've got a surgery to get to, so excuse me.

00:18:06.144 --> 00:18:08.444
Doors are closing.

00:18:16.278 --> 00:18:17.795
[Son Jeong A]

00:18:24.070 --> 00:18:26.890
So, did everything go smoothly at check-in?

00:18:26.890 --> 00:18:28.772
That story caught my eye.

00:18:28.772 --> 00:18:30.751
Right, about that...

00:18:30.751 --> 00:18:32.188
Being with someone of your stature,

00:18:32.188 --> 00:18:35.890
I always knew it wouldn't be simple.

00:18:35.890 --> 00:18:38.099
Should I come to the hotel this weekend?

00:19:10.249 --> 00:19:11.264
Hey, Mom!

00:19:11.264 --> 00:19:13.217
No dinner yet, right?

00:19:17.146 --> 00:19:18.743
What is all this?

00:19:18.743 --> 00:19:20.433
Surprise!

00:19:22.563 --> 00:19:24.645
It looks so good.

00:19:29.146 --> 00:19:31.243
Pretty impressive cooking skills, right?

00:19:31.243 --> 00:19:33.864
Grown-up or not,
at least sleep under your own roof.

00:19:33.864 --> 00:19:36.801
One more time
and every single lock code is getting reset.

00:19:36.801 --> 00:19:39.182
You're contradicting yourself, you know that?

00:19:39.182 --> 00:19:42.281
When you miss me, just be sweet about it.

00:19:42.281 --> 00:19:44.682
There's a mountain of recycling
and the balcony reeks.

00:19:44.682 --> 00:19:46.442
Nobody touched the washing machine,
so no clean towels left.

00:19:46.442 --> 00:19:47.902
Plus, zero eggs in the fridge.

00:19:47.902 --> 00:19:49.582
Oh, so this is all about housework.

00:19:49.582 --> 00:19:51.822
Look, I already tossed the trash
and scrubbed every floor.

00:19:51.822 --> 00:19:52.902
Lay off the booze.

00:19:52.902 --> 00:19:56.462
Back in the day, you always stumbled home
no matter how drunk you were.

00:19:56.462 --> 00:19:57.722
Right? That does sound like me.

00:19:57.722 --> 00:20:00.431
My internal GPS is solid,
so how did that happen...

00:20:04.063 --> 00:20:06.103
You can't leave.

00:20:08.223 --> 00:20:10.441
What's wrong? That's creepy.

00:20:15.273 --> 00:20:16.399
What?

00:20:16.399 --> 00:20:17.608
- Huh?
- What?

00:20:17.608 --> 00:20:18.820
- What?
- What?

00:20:18.820 --> 00:20:19.855
What?

00:20:19.855 --> 00:20:22.119
No!

00:20:23.563 --> 00:20:27.083
Someone's busy piecing the night back together.

00:20:38.730 --> 00:20:40.972
The aroma is already amazing.

00:20:41.605 --> 00:20:43.897
- Nice, right?
- Yes.

00:20:43.897 --> 00:20:46.143
- Thank you.
- Sure.

00:20:47.012 --> 00:20:50.313
What I'm getting at is...

00:20:50.313 --> 00:20:52.184
It'd be great if you could handle

00:20:52.184 --> 00:20:54.853
the GRO role for actress Son Jeong A.

00:20:54.853 --> 00:20:56.980
Doesn't that kind of thing

00:20:56.980 --> 00:20:58.782
normally fall under the concierge department?

00:20:58.782 --> 00:21:02.401
There's no set playbook for GRO at our hotel.

00:21:02.401 --> 00:21:05.602
Figure out your own way
to connect with the guest

00:21:05.602 --> 00:21:08.787
and deliver the best experience possible.

00:21:08.787 --> 00:21:13.271
Am I really the right person for this?

00:21:13.271 --> 00:21:15.507
Remember that thing I tell you all the time?

00:21:15.507 --> 00:21:17.688
Great hospitality isn't born

00:21:17.688 --> 00:21:19.274
out of expertise.

00:21:19.274 --> 00:21:21.971
It comes from sincerity.

00:21:23.271 --> 00:21:25.474
I know you've got this.

00:21:27.480 --> 00:21:29.930
Shopping is a big chunk of it, sure,

00:21:29.930 --> 00:21:32.098
but, beyond that...

00:21:32.098 --> 00:21:35.987
everyone's been really harsh on her lately,

00:21:35.987 --> 00:21:37.896
and you're a fan of Son Jeong A.

00:21:37.896 --> 00:21:39.355
In moments like these, a friendly face nearby

00:21:39.355 --> 00:21:42.776
could really make a difference.

00:21:42.776 --> 00:21:45.989
Here's your shot at being the ultimate fan.

00:21:48.271 --> 00:21:49.964
Understood.

00:21:49.964 --> 00:21:51.624
Good.

00:21:51.624 --> 00:21:53.521
The essentials are covered on my end,

00:21:53.521 --> 00:21:57.165
but do some digging to see
if there's anything else she wants

00:21:57.165 --> 00:21:58.645
- and get it prepared.
- Will do.

00:21:58.645 --> 00:22:00.627
For anything you're unsure about,

00:22:00.627 --> 00:22:02.797
this is the business card
for Son Jeong A's manager.

00:22:02.797 --> 00:22:05.514
Give him a call.

00:22:08.474 --> 00:22:10.063
That said,

00:22:10.063 --> 00:22:13.688
keep it professional.

00:22:13.688 --> 00:22:16.355
Right, absolutely.

00:22:16.355 --> 00:22:18.027
Sure.

00:22:29.364 --> 00:22:32.166
["Queen of Romance for 20 years now,"
every moment feels like the final one]

00:22:37.497 --> 00:22:39.040
[Never misses a chance to read while traveling]

00:22:39.040 --> 00:22:40.417
[Marguerite Duras]
[The Lover]

00:22:40.417 --> 00:22:42.544
[Wine and chocolate]

00:22:42.544 --> 00:22:44.708
[Vinyl Bill Evans jazz records]

00:22:50.135 --> 00:22:55.731
["Nothing Without Love?"
Backlash over Son Jeong A's acceptance speech]

00:22:57.208 --> 00:22:58.980
Acting and loving are the two moments

00:22:58.980 --> 00:23:00.883
where I feel truly alive,

00:23:00.883 --> 00:23:04.941
and not once have I felt embarrassed by it.

00:23:04.941 --> 00:23:07.939
Without love, I'm practically lifeless,

00:23:07.939 --> 00:23:09.696
so all that passion is something

00:23:09.696 --> 00:23:12.445
I plan to channel
into my craft for years to come.

00:23:12.445 --> 00:23:14.333
Thank you.

00:23:18.288 --> 00:23:19.289
[48th Seoul Film Awards]

00:23:19.289 --> 00:23:21.918
[Best Actress, Son Jeong A]

00:23:21.918 --> 00:23:24.260
Congratulations.

00:23:27.202 --> 00:23:31.517
Now I get why people made such a fuss.

00:23:34.389 --> 00:23:35.765
Oh, you scared me.

00:23:35.765 --> 00:23:37.946
When did you all show up?

00:23:37.946 --> 00:23:41.325
So caring about her juniors
doesn't qualify as love?

00:23:41.325 --> 00:23:44.586
Careful you don't flip from fangirl to hater.

00:23:44.586 --> 00:23:46.150
Word on the street is

00:23:46.150 --> 00:23:48.069
she exclusively talks to guys.

00:23:48.069 --> 00:23:49.897
- What?
- What?

00:23:49.897 --> 00:23:51.787
No way...

00:23:55.563 --> 00:23:58.205
Shouldn't you all be working?

00:23:58.205 --> 00:24:00.486
Talking about celebrities
is entertaining, right?

00:24:00.486 --> 00:24:02.446
Highlight of my entire day, honestly.

00:24:02.446 --> 00:24:04.813
Off to do my actual job now.

00:24:04.813 --> 00:24:07.166
Actually, there's something I need to bring up.

00:24:07.166 --> 00:24:09.464
Apparently one of the pop-up shelves
is rattling,

00:24:09.464 --> 00:24:11.347
want me to reach out to HOME
about getting it repaired?

00:24:11.347 --> 00:24:13.893
- Yeah, please do.
- Sure.

00:24:19.355 --> 00:24:22.986
I heard the soup uses seasonal ingredients.

00:24:22.986 --> 00:24:24.786
Oh, green peas?

00:24:24.786 --> 00:24:26.230
Got it.

00:24:26.230 --> 00:24:28.606
Party of two on the 2nd, 5:30 p.m.

00:24:28.606 --> 00:24:32.206
Somewhere peaceful where we can talk, please.

00:24:32.206 --> 00:24:34.288
Yes, thank you.

00:24:35.742 --> 00:24:40.503
Looks like a 46% rain forecast
for the afternoon.

00:24:41.454 --> 00:24:43.164
Might as well pack an umbrella to be safe.

00:24:43.164 --> 00:24:46.662
[2nd, 5:30 p.m., party of two, peas, umbrella]

00:24:47.521 --> 00:24:49.855
Scroll up a little.

00:24:49.855 --> 00:24:52.521
What is he up to?

00:24:52.521 --> 00:24:54.885
Beats me, did he take on something new?

00:24:54.885 --> 00:24:58.014
Let's just say this might be the biggest
undertaking of his life.

00:24:58.014 --> 00:25:01.578
By the way, pack up some tools
and make a trip to the hotel.

00:25:01.578 --> 00:25:04.019
One of the display units over there seems off.

00:25:04.019 --> 00:25:06.539
Do a full inspection of everything
while you're at it.

00:25:06.539 --> 00:25:08.280
Let me...

00:25:10.438 --> 00:25:12.619
- I'll go.
- Seriously, you?

00:25:12.619 --> 00:25:15.780
We'd be super grateful
if you're actually going yourself.

00:25:15.780 --> 00:25:17.480
Sure.

00:25:17.480 --> 00:25:19.500
Safe travels.

00:25:20.146 --> 00:25:22.044
So we're off the hook?

00:25:36.441 --> 00:25:37.541
Ui Yeong.

00:25:37.541 --> 00:25:39.396
Oh, Tae Seop.

00:25:39.396 --> 00:25:42.581
- Did you make the trip in person?
- Yeah.

00:25:42.581 --> 00:25:43.921
Everything good with you?

00:25:43.921 --> 00:25:45.361
Yeah.

00:25:45.361 --> 00:25:47.621
Actress Son Jeong A,
you know who she is, right?

00:25:47.621 --> 00:25:48.642
Of course.

00:25:48.642 --> 00:25:50.688
They put me in charge of her hotel experience,

00:25:50.688 --> 00:25:52.462
something like that.

00:25:52.462 --> 00:25:54.942
Oh, really? She's your favorite, isn't she?

00:25:54.942 --> 00:25:57.641
Right, which is exactly
why my nerves are a wreck.

00:25:57.641 --> 00:25:59.104
All day I've been digging through every article

00:25:59.104 --> 00:26:01.941
and scrolling through her posts
like it's homework.

00:26:01.941 --> 00:26:04.980
Her socials.

00:26:04.980 --> 00:26:07.146
Do you have one too?

00:26:07.146 --> 00:26:08.883
Yeah.

00:26:10.502 --> 00:26:13.006
Where do I even tap?

00:26:13.006 --> 00:26:16.543
It feels like I'm peeking
into Ui Yeong's drawer.

00:26:16.543 --> 00:26:19.393
Oh, she likes food.

00:26:23.897 --> 00:26:25.476
Gosh, look at you.

00:26:25.476 --> 00:26:28.938
You're absolutely glued
to someone else's profile.

00:26:28.938 --> 00:26:32.480
Her job is mostly
sourcing ingredients for the hotel,

00:26:32.480 --> 00:26:34.730
so there's a good chance she's already tried

00:26:34.730 --> 00:26:36.361
just about every decent spot in Seoul.

00:26:36.361 --> 00:26:40.104
An ordinary place isn't going to impress her.

00:26:40.104 --> 00:26:42.918
Maybe I need to change the reservation.

00:26:42.918 --> 00:26:46.340
Put the phone away
and pay attention to this for a sec.

00:26:46.340 --> 00:26:49.279
- It won't stop scraping against the ground.
- Sure.

00:26:49.279 --> 00:26:50.458
Could you step aside, please?

00:26:50.458 --> 00:26:51.647
Step aside?

00:26:51.647 --> 00:26:53.438
Wasn't this some pricey piece

00:26:53.438 --> 00:26:55.160
of marble shipped in from Italy?

00:26:55.160 --> 00:26:57.258
Exactly. Hold it right here like this.

00:26:57.258 --> 00:26:59.308
- Like this?
- Yeah.

00:27:05.521 --> 00:27:08.063
Perfect, that does it.

00:27:08.063 --> 00:27:09.772
Can't contain yourself

00:27:09.772 --> 00:27:11.856
thinking about the date with her?

00:27:11.856 --> 00:27:14.444
A first date is a once-in-a-lifetime thing.

00:27:14.444 --> 00:27:18.202
Planning everything out has me all giddy.

00:27:59.320 --> 00:28:01.089
[Pleased to have you, enjoy a relaxing time]

00:28:06.274 --> 00:28:08.078
Looks like it's all set.

00:28:08.078 --> 00:28:09.122
Well...

00:28:09.122 --> 00:28:11.338
Except for one last piece.

00:28:18.446 --> 00:28:20.563
My name's Lee Ui Yeong,
and I'll be looking after you

00:28:20.563 --> 00:28:22.850
for the length of your visit.

00:28:24.089 --> 00:28:25.095
Nice to meet you.

00:28:25.095 --> 00:28:26.895
I'm Son Jeong A.

00:28:27.874 --> 00:28:31.984
Take a look around, and just say the word
if something's missing.

00:28:37.763 --> 00:28:41.201
Wait, I'm in the middle of this exact book.

00:28:41.861 --> 00:28:44.723
[Love]
It's one of your favorite authors, right?

00:28:44.723 --> 00:28:47.617
I got it because the new edition just came out,

00:28:47.617 --> 00:28:49.523
but it looks like I was a step behind.

00:28:49.523 --> 00:28:52.432
I bought it the day it dropped.

00:28:56.878 --> 00:28:59.723
Most hotels go with real flowers,

00:28:59.723 --> 00:29:02.563
so this picture frame was intentional?

00:29:02.563 --> 00:29:04.676
Since you're allergic to pollen.

00:29:04.676 --> 00:29:06.702
["Nothing Without Love?"
Backlash over Son Jeong A's acceptance speech]

00:29:15.395 --> 00:29:18.225
[Allergic to pollen?]

00:29:20.136 --> 00:29:23.647
Nobody's heard me bring it up
since I hate sounding high-maintenance,

00:29:23.647 --> 00:29:26.038
but you figured it out on your own.

00:29:30.393 --> 00:29:32.044
So then,

00:29:32.647 --> 00:29:35.156
what's your take on all the gossip?

00:29:35.156 --> 00:29:36.576
Think any of it's true?

00:29:36.576 --> 00:29:38.730
Well, I...

00:29:38.730 --> 00:29:43.180
Between A, B, and C,
which one feels like true love?

00:29:46.428 --> 00:29:48.146
From where I stand,

00:29:48.146 --> 00:29:51.015
my priority is making certain

00:29:51.015 --> 00:29:53.766
that you get all the rest
and comfort you deserve

00:29:53.766 --> 00:29:56.508
while you're our guest.

00:29:56.508 --> 00:29:57.981
The general manager

00:29:57.981 --> 00:30:01.065
picked a truly sharp one for me.

00:30:01.065 --> 00:30:02.428
I'm counting on you.

00:30:02.428 --> 00:30:04.488
Thank you.

00:30:04.488 --> 00:30:05.820
Also, one more thing.

00:30:05.820 --> 00:30:07.809
Two coffees a day is non-negotiable for me.

00:30:07.809 --> 00:30:10.116
The coffee they serve here is
way too harsh for my taste, though,

00:30:10.116 --> 00:30:12.912
so could you get me beans with some acidity?

00:30:12.912 --> 00:30:16.229
A medium roast should do the trick.

00:30:16.229 --> 00:30:18.916
Also, some extra sets of sleepwear
would be great,

00:30:18.916 --> 00:30:20.450
plus an additional humidifier.

00:30:20.450 --> 00:30:22.427
Sure, I'll take care of it.

00:30:25.381 --> 00:30:27.719
[Light-medium roast with a hint of acidity]

00:30:27.719 --> 00:30:30.847
Drip bags, bright acidity, okay.

00:30:30.847 --> 00:30:33.147
Need to hurry before they close up.

00:30:39.814 --> 00:30:42.692
Last call, we're about to shut down.

00:30:42.692 --> 00:30:43.772
Hey.

00:30:43.772 --> 00:30:45.450
Bro.

00:30:58.623 --> 00:31:01.658
Since when does a scrappy theater director
drink whiskey?

00:31:01.658 --> 00:31:03.504
Did you come here for a reason?

00:31:03.504 --> 00:31:05.178
Busted.

00:31:06.647 --> 00:31:09.593
That performance on Saturday, you know the one.

00:31:09.593 --> 00:31:10.618
Yeah.

00:31:10.618 --> 00:31:12.387
I heard you're putting on a show

00:31:12.387 --> 00:31:14.778
for the Seungbo Group staff,
your theater sponsor.

00:31:14.778 --> 00:31:17.396
Get on that stage for me.

00:31:17.396 --> 00:31:19.104
Se Hyun

00:31:19.104 --> 00:31:21.877
went back home because her mom's sick.

00:31:21.877 --> 00:31:23.936
What's wrong with her?

00:31:23.936 --> 00:31:25.991
Yeah, it's pretty serious.

00:31:29.271 --> 00:31:31.456
Then I'll see you at rehearsal tomorrow.

00:31:31.456 --> 00:31:32.457
Leaving already?

00:31:32.457 --> 00:31:33.493
Yeah.

00:31:33.493 --> 00:31:35.584
This drink isn't going down right.

00:31:38.146 --> 00:31:40.756
Alright, get home safe.

00:31:45.337 --> 00:31:47.297
We're officially shutting down...

00:31:47.297 --> 00:31:48.890
Any chance I could grab some drip bags?

00:31:48.890 --> 00:31:50.269
The kind with a fruity tang.

00:31:50.269 --> 00:31:52.643
Yeah, come on in.

00:31:58.401 --> 00:31:59.530
Have you been stuck at the office all day?

00:31:59.530 --> 00:32:02.027
Yeah, things really piled up.

00:32:04.271 --> 00:32:06.281
Feeling snacky at all?

00:32:10.688 --> 00:32:14.414
Mom, I worked late
and I'm grabbing a bite before I come home.

00:32:15.967 --> 00:32:17.476
Here.

00:32:17.476 --> 00:32:19.704
I'm not drinking for a while.

00:32:19.704 --> 00:32:20.876
How come?

00:32:20.876 --> 00:32:22.667
There's work in the morning,

00:32:22.667 --> 00:32:25.299
plus mom's been keeping
an eye on me these days.

00:32:31.271 --> 00:32:33.857
Are we even allowed to snack like this in here?

00:32:33.857 --> 00:32:35.056
Totally fine.

00:32:35.056 --> 00:32:36.176
How about some tunes?

00:32:36.176 --> 00:32:38.230
Sounds perfect.

00:32:38.976 --> 00:32:40.766
It pays to know someone at a cafe.

00:32:40.766 --> 00:32:42.022
[A Season Called You]

00:33:02.313 --> 00:33:03.540
Hey.

00:33:03.540 --> 00:33:05.947
I'm knocking one meal off my tab with this.

00:33:05.947 --> 00:33:08.313
Only two more to go.

00:33:08.313 --> 00:33:10.346
You're really keeping count. So petty.

00:33:10.346 --> 00:33:13.216
Compared to everything I've done,
this barely registers.

00:33:13.216 --> 00:33:15.521
For someone saying that,
you sure seem to be enjoying it.

00:33:15.521 --> 00:33:17.144
You've got some sauce there.

00:33:18.146 --> 00:33:19.222
Plus,

00:33:19.222 --> 00:33:20.987
it's not like anyone forced you to jump in.

00:33:20.987 --> 00:33:25.068
Volunteering first
and then billing me in food is pretty low.

00:33:25.730 --> 00:33:27.288
Well, that's...

00:33:27.288 --> 00:33:28.290
Fair point.

00:33:30.086 --> 00:33:32.659
You've got some on you, too.

00:33:35.480 --> 00:33:39.154
Minding my own business is kind of my thing,

00:33:39.154 --> 00:33:41.585
yet somehow your stuff always pulls me in.

00:33:43.730 --> 00:33:45.464
See?

00:33:53.063 --> 00:33:54.116
Hey.

00:33:54.116 --> 00:33:57.718
Talk like that in front of other people
and they'll read into it.

00:33:57.718 --> 00:34:00.312
Seriously, your concept
of personal space is wild.

00:34:01.480 --> 00:34:03.690
Call it a misunderstanding if you want,

00:34:04.976 --> 00:34:07.277
but maybe some of it isn't so far off.

00:34:09.190 --> 00:34:10.864
What?

00:34:12.438 --> 00:34:15.901
It seems like you keep treating me
like just anybody,

00:34:15.901 --> 00:34:18.480
but whether I was
a last-minute stand-in or not,

00:34:18.480 --> 00:34:20.825
the two of us did go on that date.

00:34:20.825 --> 00:34:23.538
Things have been building between us.

00:34:23.538 --> 00:34:27.521
Every moment with you has been a good time,

00:34:27.521 --> 00:34:29.341
or am I the only one who feels that way?

00:34:32.130 --> 00:34:33.678
What?

00:34:35.513 --> 00:34:38.021
Don't overthink it.

00:34:38.021 --> 00:34:39.635
All I'm saying is...

00:34:39.635 --> 00:34:42.729
my days have been way more interesting
since you came around.

00:34:43.355 --> 00:34:44.575
Just keep eating.

00:34:44.575 --> 00:34:46.934
Take your time digesting that.

00:34:46.934 --> 00:34:48.860
Oh, man.

00:35:00.723 --> 00:35:02.146
How are you getting home?

00:35:02.146 --> 00:35:03.257
I called a cab.

00:35:03.257 --> 00:35:05.161
It'll be here soon.

00:35:05.161 --> 00:35:07.921
I've got to head to rehearsal too.

00:35:09.355 --> 00:35:11.355
- Go home safe.
- Yeah.

00:35:11.355 --> 00:35:13.230
Let's grab a meal again later.

00:35:13.230 --> 00:35:15.429
Sure, take care.

00:35:20.438 --> 00:35:22.102
Bye.

00:35:40.980 --> 00:35:43.373
What was that, all of a sudden?

00:35:43.992 --> 00:35:47.711
Since when is "I enjoy your company"
not the same as "I have feelings for you"?

00:35:52.521 --> 00:35:53.897
[Song Tae Seop]

00:35:53.897 --> 00:35:55.380
You did great today.

00:35:55.380 --> 00:35:57.705
I can't wait for the weekend to get here.

00:35:57.705 --> 00:35:59.639
Good night.

00:36:04.164 --> 00:36:05.412
Thank you.

00:36:05.412 --> 00:36:07.153
Good night to you too, Tae Seop.

00:36:07.153 --> 00:36:09.232
See you soon.

00:36:17.230 --> 00:36:18.772
- Come in.
- Okay.

00:36:18.772 --> 00:36:20.861
- Let me take this call.
- Sure.

00:36:20.861 --> 00:36:22.396
Yeah.

00:36:22.396 --> 00:36:24.414
What do you mean, casting?

00:36:25.492 --> 00:36:27.663
Who told you to go ahead
and pull that off on your own?

00:36:27.663 --> 00:36:30.682
It's just a show for the staff.

00:36:30.682 --> 00:36:32.772
I'm the wife of a group chairman,

00:36:32.772 --> 00:36:33.963
and I can't even sponsor it?

00:36:33.963 --> 00:36:36.462
Drop it. I can't go.

00:36:36.462 --> 00:36:38.782
Dr. Shin is coming tomorrow.

00:36:38.782 --> 00:36:41.922
I've got a ton of stuff to sort out with him.

00:36:41.922 --> 00:36:42.923
My head is spinning.

00:36:42.923 --> 00:36:44.603
For now, shoot me the location.

00:36:44.603 --> 00:36:47.062
Yeah, okay, I'll send it.

00:36:50.435 --> 00:36:51.600
So the thing is,

00:36:51.600 --> 00:36:55.147
- I have a small favor to run by you.
- Of course, what is it?

00:36:55.147 --> 00:36:56.647
I'll send you the address,

00:36:56.647 --> 00:36:58.902
so could you deliver
a flower basket there tomorrow?

00:36:58.902 --> 00:37:02.702
It's an important performance,
but I can't make it.

00:37:03.813 --> 00:37:05.977
Also,

00:37:05.977 --> 00:37:07.008
take this card with you.

00:37:07.008 --> 00:37:08.040
Got it.

00:37:08.040 --> 00:37:09.118
No need to stay for the performance.

00:37:09.118 --> 00:37:11.063
Just drop off the flowers.

00:37:11.063 --> 00:37:12.107
Of course, no problem.

00:37:12.107 --> 00:37:14.980
Also, I'm planning
to have a guest over tomorrow night

00:37:14.980 --> 00:37:16.584
to share a meal.

00:37:16.584 --> 00:37:17.967
How many guests?

00:37:17.967 --> 00:37:19.251
Just one.

00:37:19.251 --> 00:37:22.673
He'll be here around 7 p.m., and for the menu,

00:37:22.673 --> 00:37:24.842
something Western that pairs well with wine.

00:37:24.842 --> 00:37:26.252
I'll leave it to you.

00:37:26.252 --> 00:37:29.492
Absolutely, everything will be set
the moment your guest walks in.

00:37:29.492 --> 00:37:31.031
He'll also be spending the night.

00:37:31.031 --> 00:37:33.052
Make sure discretion is a top priority.

00:37:33.052 --> 00:37:35.110
Absolutely, I'll see to it.

00:37:39.980 --> 00:37:42.071
Should I have bought two?

00:37:42.071 --> 00:37:43.252
Think it'll be enough?

00:37:43.252 --> 00:37:47.289
It's not like Tae Seop is
some big eater or spender.

00:37:50.099 --> 00:37:53.169
You sure he has no desires?

00:37:54.480 --> 00:37:56.381
Did we come to the wrong place?

00:37:59.063 --> 00:38:01.094
Wet wipes.

00:38:01.855 --> 00:38:04.063
Hydrogen peroxide. Band-aids.

00:38:04.063 --> 00:38:06.207
Are you going to boot camp?

00:38:06.207 --> 00:38:07.220
Blanket.

00:38:07.220 --> 00:38:09.959
This is for a date, right?

00:38:09.959 --> 00:38:13.230
Anything could come up when you're out,

00:38:13.230 --> 00:38:16.563
so it makes sense to have these on hand.

00:38:16.563 --> 00:38:19.063
Sua, put that down,
wash your hands, and come eat pizza.

00:38:19.063 --> 00:38:20.947
Sure.

00:38:26.785 --> 00:38:29.626
I've never seen anyone
prepare this hard for a date.

00:38:29.626 --> 00:38:31.645
Is this anxiety or straight-up insanity?

00:38:31.645 --> 00:38:33.745
It's pure anticipation.

00:38:33.745 --> 00:38:35.366
Dad!

00:38:35.366 --> 00:38:37.589
Look at this!

00:38:39.271 --> 00:38:40.584
A timetable.

00:38:40.584 --> 00:38:43.423
[Dinner, Coffee Time, Movie, Drive Home]

00:38:44.521 --> 00:38:46.298
This isn't a dream, right?

00:38:46.298 --> 00:38:49.768
Never believed anyone like this
was real until now.

00:38:50.588 --> 00:38:51.595
Hey Sua,

00:38:51.595 --> 00:38:55.333
once you finish eating,
mind helping me choose what to wear?

00:38:55.333 --> 00:38:57.126
Okay.

00:38:57.126 --> 00:38:59.327
Sua, I'm cooler than him, aren't I?

00:38:59.327 --> 00:39:01.897
No, he wins by a mile.

00:39:01.897 --> 00:39:03.727
That hurts!

00:39:03.727 --> 00:39:05.438
I thought I was dreaming.

00:39:05.438 --> 00:39:07.118
Look at this.

00:39:28.230 --> 00:39:29.385
Seung Jun.

00:39:29.385 --> 00:39:31.326
Don't you think it's boiling in here?

00:39:31.326 --> 00:39:33.188
That's just proof

00:39:33.188 --> 00:39:35.506
that we worked hard today.

00:39:35.506 --> 00:39:36.974
I mean, that's not the point.

00:39:36.974 --> 00:39:39.626
Pretty sure the air conditioning is dead.

00:39:39.626 --> 00:39:40.747
What are you talking about?

00:39:40.747 --> 00:39:42.946
They literally just repaired it.

00:39:44.480 --> 00:39:45.640
Wait, seriously?

00:39:45.640 --> 00:39:47.167
Not a single bit of cool air. Nothing.

00:39:47.167 --> 00:39:49.285
See? Told you.

00:40:03.253 --> 00:40:04.313
This piece of junk...

00:40:04.313 --> 00:40:06.636
The repair bills alone
cost more than a new one.

00:40:11.563 --> 00:40:13.378
Oh, hello?

00:40:13.378 --> 00:40:15.218
Oh, hi, Hyun Min.

00:40:15.218 --> 00:40:17.473
My schedule freed up early,

00:40:17.473 --> 00:40:19.498
which means I could see you
earlier than planned.

00:40:19.498 --> 00:40:21.138
Right,

00:40:21.138 --> 00:40:24.498
but our gym's AC just broke down
and it's chaos here,

00:40:24.498 --> 00:40:26.599
so I don't think I can step away right now.

00:40:26.599 --> 00:40:28.285
Gosh.

00:40:28.285 --> 00:40:30.639
Isn't it like a furnace in there
without air conditioning?

00:40:30.639 --> 00:40:33.021
Absolutely, we're practically
in a hot spring right now

00:40:33.021 --> 00:40:35.480
and honestly I might pass out from the heat.

00:40:35.480 --> 00:40:37.868
Give me a minute to handle this,

00:40:37.868 --> 00:40:39.665
then I'll reach out again.

00:40:39.665 --> 00:40:40.706
- Okay.
- I'm really sorry.

00:40:40.706 --> 00:40:42.630
No worries at all.

00:40:52.098 --> 00:40:53.099
You're hot, right?

00:40:53.099 --> 00:40:54.183
I'm so sorry.

00:40:54.183 --> 00:40:55.199
Sorry about this.

00:40:55.199 --> 00:40:56.558
Take this towel, please.

00:40:56.558 --> 00:40:58.188
Apologies, you must be melting.

00:40:58.188 --> 00:41:00.023
- Grab a towel.
- Unbearable, right?

00:41:01.647 --> 00:41:03.779
Right now it's like military training in here.

00:41:03.779 --> 00:41:05.854
- I'm so sorry.
- My clothes are drenched all the way through.

00:41:05.854 --> 00:41:07.277
I apologize.

00:41:07.277 --> 00:41:08.899
Please take it easy, it's risky in this heat.

00:41:08.899 --> 00:41:10.079
Your memberships will be extended on us.

00:41:10.079 --> 00:41:11.910
Sorry about this.

00:41:30.924 --> 00:41:32.761
Let's cool you down.

00:41:32.761 --> 00:41:34.849
Hyun Min.

00:41:37.680 --> 00:41:40.141
You must be hot. Here, have one of these.

00:41:40.141 --> 00:41:41.473
Right.

00:41:41.473 --> 00:41:43.811
What flavor can I get you?

00:41:43.811 --> 00:41:45.761
Thank you.

00:41:45.761 --> 00:41:47.230
Wait a sec.

00:41:47.230 --> 00:41:49.106
I feel like I've seen you before.

00:41:49.106 --> 00:41:49.859
Are you okay?

00:41:49.859 --> 00:41:50.855
Don't I know you from somewhere?

00:41:50.855 --> 00:41:52.688
I'm sorry.

00:41:52.688 --> 00:41:55.360
- Don't worry about your membership.
- Well...

00:41:55.360 --> 00:41:57.300
Can't say I recognize you.

00:41:57.300 --> 00:41:58.949
You're quite the smooth talker.

00:41:58.949 --> 00:42:00.480
Oh, I didn't mean that.

00:42:00.480 --> 00:42:01.980
Seriously,

00:42:01.980 --> 00:42:03.579
you're sweating way too much.

00:42:03.579 --> 00:42:05.205
Let me get you

00:42:05.205 --> 00:42:08.063
some extra towels.

00:42:08.063 --> 00:42:09.884
Right, thanks.

00:42:13.279 --> 00:42:14.465
I'll head out first.

00:42:14.465 --> 00:42:15.841
Yeah, good work today.

00:42:15.841 --> 00:42:18.772
[Closed for weekend AC repairs]

00:42:18.772 --> 00:42:21.388
Get some rest, Seung Jun.

00:42:21.388 --> 00:42:23.265
Will do.

00:42:23.265 --> 00:42:25.567
He puts his heart into everything.

00:42:27.230 --> 00:42:28.903
Here.

00:42:33.855 --> 00:42:35.799
Appreciate you coming by today.

00:42:35.799 --> 00:42:38.238
But how did you know to come?

00:42:38.238 --> 00:42:40.640
Your shirt has it plastered across the front.

00:42:40.640 --> 00:42:42.660
Deukgeun Deukgeun Gym.

00:42:42.660 --> 00:42:44.720
That whole stripping moment is
burned into my brain.

00:42:44.720 --> 00:42:47.122
Pervert.

00:42:47.122 --> 00:42:49.340
You like this pervert, though.

00:42:57.093 --> 00:42:59.359
Wait, is that one strawberry?

00:42:59.359 --> 00:43:01.185
Let me try a taste.

00:43:27.355 --> 00:43:30.798
It's still a date, so...

00:43:31.551 --> 00:43:33.551
Go with something colorful?

00:43:36.313 --> 00:43:37.691
No.

00:43:37.691 --> 00:43:40.553
Looking like I put in
too much effort would be...

00:43:40.553 --> 00:43:42.644
Such an amateur thing.

00:43:46.765 --> 00:43:48.144
Maybe a dress?

00:43:48.144 --> 00:43:50.563
A dress?

00:43:50.563 --> 00:43:52.570
How about jeans?

00:44:12.939 --> 00:44:15.421
Perfect.

00:44:15.421 --> 00:44:17.845
I look casual and cute.

00:44:24.145 --> 00:44:26.145
Thank you.

00:44:31.310 --> 00:44:33.353
- Have a wonderful time.
- Thanks.

00:44:33.353 --> 00:44:34.813
Hello.

00:44:34.813 --> 00:44:36.367
- Have a wonderful time.
- Thanks.

00:44:36.367 --> 00:44:37.208
- Hello.
- Hello.

00:44:37.208 --> 00:44:39.328
Would it be possible
to pass these flowers along?

00:44:39.328 --> 00:44:41.221
[Coat Check]
Absolutely. Leave them with me,

00:44:41.221 --> 00:44:42.939
I'll make sure
they get there once the curtain falls.

00:44:42.939 --> 00:44:44.330
And who should I bring them to?

00:44:44.330 --> 00:44:47.333
Hang on one second.

00:44:49.537 --> 00:44:50.555
[To Ji Su, congrats on the show. Need to talk]

00:44:50.555 --> 00:44:52.230
[I'm at The Hills Seoul. Come see me.
From Son Jeong A]

00:44:52.230 --> 00:44:53.549
Ji Su?

00:44:53.549 --> 00:44:56.217
Oh, you mean Shin Ji Su?

00:44:57.855 --> 00:44:59.350
Yes, Shin Ji Su.

00:44:59.350 --> 00:45:01.639
Oh, got it.

00:45:04.605 --> 00:45:07.521
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

00:45:07.521 --> 00:45:10.977
Hello, let me check your ticket.

00:45:10.977 --> 00:45:12.021
Have a wonderful time.

00:45:12.021 --> 00:45:15.230
- Thanks.
- Thanks.

00:45:15.230 --> 00:45:17.238
Thank you.

00:45:17.855 --> 00:45:19.598
[The Seagull]

00:45:20.776 --> 00:45:22.438
[The Seagull]

00:45:22.438 --> 00:45:25.030
Wait, Son Jeong A and Shin Ji Su

00:45:25.030 --> 00:45:27.605
are actually connected?

00:45:27.605 --> 00:45:29.709
Could it be...

00:45:34.873 --> 00:45:38.248
[The queen's long list of men]

00:45:39.297 --> 00:45:40.754
Sources claim she's living

00:45:40.754 --> 00:45:43.188
with surgeon A,
a former affair turned domestic partner,

00:45:43.188 --> 00:45:45.634
while also seeing director B
secretly at a high-end hotel,

00:45:45.634 --> 00:45:48.436
and financially supporting model C
on top of all that.

00:45:49.180 --> 00:45:50.216
[She bankrolled Model C]

00:45:50.216 --> 00:45:52.565
[With her long history of flings,
this scandal is just the beginning]

00:46:19.146 --> 00:46:21.339
Ui Yeong.

00:46:21.339 --> 00:46:23.466
New hairstyle?

00:46:23.466 --> 00:46:25.188
Where are your glasses?

00:46:25.188 --> 00:46:26.759
I put in a little effort.

00:46:26.759 --> 00:46:29.178
It's our first date.

00:46:30.178 --> 00:46:33.184
I should've dressed up more.

00:46:33.184 --> 00:46:35.998
You're looking beautiful,
same as every other day.

00:46:35.998 --> 00:46:38.444
Same as every day?

00:46:40.522 --> 00:46:41.818
Ready to grab some food?

00:46:41.818 --> 00:46:44.179
There's a place I found
that's just around the corner.

00:46:44.179 --> 00:46:46.945
A Michelin one-star chef just launched it.

00:46:46.945 --> 00:46:47.779
[Shut for the day, apologies for any trouble]

00:46:47.779 --> 00:46:49.831
It's closed?

00:46:52.284 --> 00:46:53.558
[This is Firenze. We sincerely apologize
to all our scheduled guests]

00:46:53.558 --> 00:46:56.295
Oh, it's closed...

00:47:00.396 --> 00:47:03.378
I actually have a backup plan, just in case.

00:47:03.378 --> 00:47:05.005
It's a five-minute walk from here.

00:47:05.005 --> 00:47:07.549
No reservation, but we're early enough that

00:47:07.549 --> 00:47:09.725
there probably won't be a wait.

00:47:11.139 --> 00:47:13.014
Lee Hui Jin.

00:47:13.014 --> 00:47:14.517
Is Lee Hui Jin here?

00:47:14.517 --> 00:47:16.649
Please come in.

00:47:23.883 --> 00:47:26.651
Standing through this entire line might mean

00:47:26.651 --> 00:47:28.843
we end up late for the film.

00:47:28.843 --> 00:47:31.289
Well, in that case...

00:47:33.604 --> 00:47:35.438
Tae Seop.

00:47:35.438 --> 00:47:37.454
The vibe isn't anything special,

00:47:37.454 --> 00:47:40.376
but I know a spot near here with amazing food.

00:47:40.376 --> 00:47:42.303
Should we head there instead?

00:47:42.303 --> 00:47:45.301
- Yeah, sounds good.
- Okay.

00:47:51.021 --> 00:47:52.685
Right.

00:47:59.104 --> 00:48:00.651
What?

00:48:05.614 --> 00:48:09.402
- Does this rock back and forth a bit?
- A little.

00:48:09.402 --> 00:48:11.634
- It's hot.
- Thank you.

00:48:11.634 --> 00:48:12.974
- Be careful.
- Thanks.

00:48:12.974 --> 00:48:15.313
Move to that side if it bothers you.

00:48:15.313 --> 00:48:17.543
I'm good right here.

00:48:20.647 --> 00:48:23.127
Being here with you is so strange.

00:48:23.127 --> 00:48:24.605
Since our vendors are in the area,

00:48:24.605 --> 00:48:26.980
this place has always been
a work lunch spot for me.

00:48:26.980 --> 00:48:28.763
I see.

00:48:29.464 --> 00:48:31.265
It looks delicious.

00:48:35.196 --> 00:48:37.694
If you do it like this,
you save the roof of your mouth

00:48:37.694 --> 00:48:39.063
and you can eat faster too.

00:48:39.063 --> 00:48:40.775
Got it.

00:48:47.396 --> 00:48:49.116
Thanks.

00:48:49.116 --> 00:48:51.077
Go ahead, dig in.

00:48:58.109 --> 00:48:59.717
- Seriously, this is incredible.
- Right?

00:48:59.717 --> 00:49:01.671
What a relief.

00:49:04.688 --> 00:49:06.842
It's good.

00:49:08.521 --> 00:49:10.897
That was a great meal.

00:49:10.897 --> 00:49:13.015
Stay seated for a second.

00:49:50.063 --> 00:49:52.179
- All done.
- All done.

00:49:55.471 --> 00:49:57.010
Those are some serious skills.

00:49:57.010 --> 00:49:58.512
Just a quick fix.

00:49:58.512 --> 00:50:01.264
That was totally something.

00:50:01.264 --> 00:50:05.067
What got you into building furniture?

00:50:06.185 --> 00:50:08.632
We went through a period
where our house had no kitchen table.

00:50:08.632 --> 00:50:10.951
Our family hit hard times out of nowhere.

00:50:10.951 --> 00:50:14.491
After that, so much just slowly faded away.

00:50:14.491 --> 00:50:17.021
Sitting down for dinner stopped happening,

00:50:17.021 --> 00:50:18.573
nobody talked anymore,

00:50:18.573 --> 00:50:20.744
and being around each other
became uncomfortable.

00:50:20.744 --> 00:50:23.840
That's when it hit me
that furniture is more than just objects.

00:50:23.840 --> 00:50:27.499
Seeing it through that lens
made it matter so much more.

00:50:27.499 --> 00:50:28.955
Making a real difference
felt like the right path.

00:50:28.955 --> 00:50:31.047
That whole twenties idealism, you know?

00:50:31.047 --> 00:50:32.714
I see.

00:50:32.714 --> 00:50:36.466
After I started the company,
all I did was work myself to the bone.

00:50:36.466 --> 00:50:38.574
What were your twenties like?

00:50:38.574 --> 00:50:40.634
With a personality like yours,
you probably had tons of friends.

00:50:40.634 --> 00:50:42.934
Not really, actually.

00:50:42.934 --> 00:50:45.308
Growing up without much to spare meant

00:50:45.308 --> 00:50:47.294
all I could focus on was my own survival.

00:50:47.294 --> 00:50:49.104
Hiding behind my own hardships,

00:50:49.104 --> 00:50:51.334
I just assumed
everyone else could tough it out too.

00:50:51.334 --> 00:50:54.193
So you had those days as well.

00:50:54.193 --> 00:50:56.230
There aren't a lot of good memories
from back then.

00:50:56.230 --> 00:50:58.188
Not a single vacation, ever.

00:50:58.188 --> 00:51:01.855
And as for romance, I kept my guard up,
telling myself the timing was wrong.

00:51:01.855 --> 00:51:02.928
That's alright.

00:51:02.928 --> 00:51:06.212
You can do
all the things you missed out on now.

00:51:08.146 --> 00:51:09.688
Exactly.

00:51:09.688 --> 00:51:13.308
Which is why I'm really happy
with how things are these days.

00:51:13.308 --> 00:51:16.597
I'm glad I met you now.

00:51:45.897 --> 00:51:47.688
The whole idea of love...

00:51:47.688 --> 00:51:49.839
it's so unpredictable.

00:51:51.688 --> 00:51:53.188
Even so,

00:51:53.188 --> 00:51:56.971
I'm ready to take that leap of faith again.

00:51:59.730 --> 00:52:01.763
Why are you crying?

00:52:01.763 --> 00:52:02.927
Are you sad?

00:52:02.927 --> 00:52:05.188
It's not that, I just...

00:52:05.188 --> 00:52:08.232
- My eyes...
- Do your eyes hurt?

00:52:08.980 --> 00:52:11.026
Come on, let's step out for now.

00:52:23.647 --> 00:52:25.897
Are you okay?

00:52:25.897 --> 00:52:28.063
Since I barely ever put contacts in,

00:52:28.063 --> 00:52:30.550
I think something got stuck. Kind of burns.

00:52:30.550 --> 00:52:33.157
That doesn't seem minor at all.
They're super bloodshot.

00:52:33.157 --> 00:52:34.438
Turn this way.

00:52:34.438 --> 00:52:36.302
What?

00:52:37.396 --> 00:52:39.221
Face me.

00:52:44.845 --> 00:52:46.313
Leaving the lenses in is a bad idea.

00:52:46.313 --> 00:52:48.898
Get them out as fast as you can.

00:52:58.396 --> 00:52:59.407
Feeling any better?

00:52:59.407 --> 00:53:00.827
Are they out? How's it now?

00:53:00.827 --> 00:53:02.688
- Way better already.
- Yeah.

00:53:02.688 --> 00:53:04.366
Want to head back inside?

00:53:04.366 --> 00:53:06.086
Back in there?

00:53:06.086 --> 00:53:08.226
Your vision's basically gone at this point.

00:53:08.226 --> 00:53:10.907
We can catch the film later.
Right now, let's just get you home.

00:53:10.907 --> 00:53:11.986
No.

00:53:11.986 --> 00:53:14.335
I can't do that.
We have to watch a movie this time.

00:53:14.335 --> 00:53:17.426
With your eyes in that condition, though...

00:53:18.063 --> 00:53:20.255
Then...

00:53:20.255 --> 00:53:23.133
How about we watch something at my apartment?

00:53:23.133 --> 00:53:24.772
Your apartment?

00:53:24.772 --> 00:53:26.230
Oh, I mean,

00:53:26.230 --> 00:53:28.089
I'm not suggesting anything weird.

00:53:28.089 --> 00:53:31.023
Putting things off again
just isn't something I want to do.

00:53:33.813 --> 00:53:36.445
Then should we grab some popcorn too?

00:53:37.063 --> 00:53:39.110
Sure.

00:53:39.110 --> 00:53:41.237
Right.

00:53:41.237 --> 00:53:44.286
Grab my arm and stay right behind me.

00:53:56.125 --> 00:53:57.505
Got it.

00:53:57.505 --> 00:53:59.002
Yeah.

00:53:59.002 --> 00:54:01.215
The designated driver will be here soon.

00:54:01.215 --> 00:54:02.246
I'm sorry.

00:54:02.246 --> 00:54:05.885
Got my license and everything,
just never been behind the wheel.

00:54:05.885 --> 00:54:07.810
No worries.

00:54:10.138 --> 00:54:12.690
I love this song.

00:54:13.365 --> 00:54:14.465
Same here.

00:54:14.465 --> 00:54:16.026
Really?

00:55:12.075 --> 00:55:13.230
Bravo!

00:55:13.230 --> 00:55:15.627
You were amazing!

00:55:17.521 --> 00:55:19.040
- Nice work tonight.
- You too.

00:55:19.040 --> 00:55:20.855
- Stop standing around and get out here.
- Good work.

00:55:20.855 --> 00:55:22.213
- Good job.
- Good job.

00:55:22.213 --> 00:55:24.438
- Nice work.
- Nice work.

00:55:24.438 --> 00:55:25.521
Ji Su.

00:55:25.521 --> 00:55:28.567
Someone sent you flowers.
Make sure you grab them.

00:55:28.567 --> 00:55:30.225
Thanks.

00:55:38.142 --> 00:55:39.368
Congrats on the show.

00:55:39.368 --> 00:55:41.107
I have something important to tell you.

00:55:41.107 --> 00:55:43.656
I'm at The Hills Seoul, so come see me.

00:55:47.568 --> 00:55:49.313
Excuse me, Shin Ji Su.

00:55:49.313 --> 00:55:51.129
I'm reporter Kim Ji Young from Dailing.

00:55:51.129 --> 00:55:54.828
You're the model C
from the Son Jeong A rumors, correct?

00:55:54.828 --> 00:55:57.108
How exactly do you know Son Jeong A?

00:55:57.108 --> 00:55:59.008
There's no relationship.

00:55:59.008 --> 00:56:01.206
Stay away from me from now on.

00:56:01.206 --> 00:56:02.667
Our sources say
the largest backer of the theater company

00:56:02.667 --> 00:56:04.569
turns out to be the Seungbo Group.

00:56:04.569 --> 00:56:08.298
Apparently Son Jeong A and the chairman's wife
are very close.

00:56:08.298 --> 00:56:09.429
Did you know about that?

00:56:09.429 --> 00:56:11.509
Particularly in arts and culture,

00:56:11.509 --> 00:56:14.648
her involvement reportedly
goes well beyond just advice.

00:56:14.648 --> 00:56:16.765
What?

00:56:16.765 --> 00:56:18.308
Did the two of you

00:56:18.308 --> 00:56:21.063
have some sort of deal

00:56:21.063 --> 00:56:24.780
tied to the theater's sponsorship money?

00:56:27.204 --> 00:56:28.738
Give me two months and it's finished.

00:56:28.738 --> 00:56:30.480
Hey!

00:56:30.480 --> 00:56:32.116
Ji Su, what's wrong?

00:56:32.116 --> 00:56:34.199
Are you out of your mind?

00:56:34.199 --> 00:56:35.988
That whole thing today was planned
to get me onstage, wasn't it?

00:56:35.988 --> 00:56:37.928
Yeah, that's called deliberate.
Nobody buys it as luck.

00:56:37.928 --> 00:56:39.467
You're twisting my words.

00:56:39.467 --> 00:56:43.917
My paychecks, my meals, all of it
came from Son Jeong A's pocket!

00:56:43.917 --> 00:56:45.230
Is this really how you treat me?

00:56:45.230 --> 00:56:47.915
The chairman's wife at Seungbo Group
backs us because she believes in what we do.

00:56:47.915 --> 00:56:48.734
Believes in us?

00:56:48.734 --> 00:56:52.508
Who throws money at a theater company
that doesn't turn a profit

00:56:52.508 --> 00:56:55.720
and can't be bothered to show up
for one performance?

00:56:55.720 --> 00:56:59.018
Cut the crap with your oversized ego already.

00:56:59.018 --> 00:57:00.391
It's not about your paycheck.

00:57:00.391 --> 00:57:02.685
It's our theater rent, the crew's wages,

00:57:02.685 --> 00:57:04.834
food, costumes, props.

00:57:04.834 --> 00:57:06.146
Every last one of us
has staked our lives on this,

00:57:06.146 --> 00:57:07.975
so if there's a chance to move up, we take it.

00:57:07.975 --> 00:57:09.695
The place you treat like some bunker to hide in

00:57:09.695 --> 00:57:12.111
is the stage we've been dying to stand on.

00:57:12.111 --> 00:57:14.155
Keep straddling the fence like that

00:57:14.155 --> 00:57:16.373
and you might as well walk away for good.

00:57:35.009 --> 00:57:36.211
Fine. I'm out.

00:57:36.211 --> 00:57:38.479
Hey, what are you doing?

00:57:41.019 --> 00:57:42.983
I said I'm done.

00:57:44.731 --> 00:57:47.321
You can't just say you're quitting.

00:58:05.293 --> 00:58:07.466
I'm going to the hotel now.

00:58:15.528 --> 00:58:17.972
Give me a sec, I need to grab my glasses.

00:58:17.972 --> 00:58:20.208
Just relax on the sofa.

00:58:20.208 --> 00:58:21.772
Sure.

00:58:36.366 --> 00:58:39.039
This place is spotless.

00:59:01.888 --> 00:59:07.359
[Dinner, Coffee Time, Movie, Drive Home]

00:59:13.521 --> 00:59:17.286
So every single detail was mapped in advance?

00:59:17.945 --> 00:59:19.701
Thing is,

00:59:19.701 --> 00:59:22.120
not a single thing followed the script...

00:59:22.120 --> 00:59:24.126
Yeah, not a single thing.

00:59:27.647 --> 00:59:29.396
Even so,

00:59:29.396 --> 00:59:31.258
I had an amazing time.

00:59:42.271 --> 00:59:44.146
Feel free to look around if you're bored.

00:59:44.146 --> 00:59:46.641
Oh, sure.

01:00:16.549 --> 01:00:18.639
Oh, wait.

01:00:21.396 --> 01:00:23.457
For drinks,

01:00:23.457 --> 01:00:26.837
what would you like?
Water, sparkling water, soda, or green tea?

01:00:26.837 --> 01:00:29.063
Actually... Just water!

01:00:29.063 --> 01:00:30.859
Ice cold!

01:00:31.647 --> 01:00:33.737
Need to snap out of it...

01:00:53.528 --> 01:00:56.688
What kind of movies do you like?

01:00:56.688 --> 01:00:58.104
Honestly, I'll watch

01:00:58.104 --> 01:01:01.108
just about anything as long as it's not scary.

01:01:01.108 --> 01:01:03.456
Horror's off the table for you?

01:01:04.438 --> 01:01:06.396
My heart literally

01:01:06.396 --> 01:01:09.088
can't take that kind of stress.

01:01:09.088 --> 01:01:11.968
Are you into horror films?

01:01:11.968 --> 01:01:13.189
I just watch them.

01:01:13.189 --> 01:01:16.564
Growing up, my father always said
ghosts aren't the ones to worry about.

01:01:16.564 --> 01:01:19.897
Once he told me humans are the real threat,

01:01:19.897 --> 01:01:22.077
nothing on screen could rattle me.

01:01:23.438 --> 01:01:25.872
Those are words to live by.

01:01:29.855 --> 01:01:33.338
People say this one's great.

01:01:35.250 --> 01:01:36.348
[Single in Seoul]
This one?

01:01:36.348 --> 01:01:37.968
Yeah.

01:01:39.230 --> 01:01:40.980
Then,

01:01:40.980 --> 01:01:43.306
should I turn off the lights?

01:01:46.347 --> 01:01:48.273
Sure.

01:01:53.146 --> 01:01:55.199
Hotel work really takes a toll on your hands.

01:01:55.199 --> 01:01:57.154
Make sure you keep them moisturized.

01:01:59.152 --> 01:02:01.908
If there's one thing a hotel never runs out of,
it's lotion.

01:02:06.688 --> 01:02:08.521
What a hidden gem

01:02:08.521 --> 01:02:10.375
of a name.

01:02:57.647 --> 01:02:59.855
Well...

01:02:59.855 --> 01:03:01.802
Ui Yeong...

01:03:02.563 --> 01:03:03.883
Yes?

01:03:03.883 --> 01:03:06.709
There's something I want to say.

01:03:38.396 --> 01:03:40.674
- Oh, son.
- Mother.

01:03:44.556 --> 01:03:46.813
Oh my goodness.

01:03:46.813 --> 01:03:48.007
Are you okay?

01:03:48.007 --> 01:03:49.317
You're not hurt, are you?

01:03:49.317 --> 01:03:51.813
Oh my. Goodness.

01:03:51.813 --> 01:03:53.616
I'm sorry.

01:03:53.616 --> 01:03:54.817
No, it's okay.

01:03:54.817 --> 01:03:58.775
Nice to meet you. Hello.

01:04:00.855 --> 01:04:02.897
What?

01:04:02.897 --> 01:04:04.736
My regular girl?

01:04:04.736 --> 01:04:06.578
Oh, it's you.

01:04:11.063 --> 01:04:12.616
He was right.

01:04:12.616 --> 01:04:15.375
Humans really are the scariest of all.

01:04:31.217 --> 01:04:34.804
[What's done is done, spilled and all]

01:04:34.804 --> 01:04:38.557
[A once-in-a-lifetime mission!]

01:04:38.557 --> 01:04:42.235
[I keep stepping in]

01:04:45.815 --> 01:04:49.485
[Glad we met now]

01:04:49.485 --> 01:04:53.656
[What you mean to me]

01:04:53.656 --> 01:04:56.750
[Shall I turn off the lights?]

01:04:58.039 --> 01:05:00.189
Dating isn't what it used to be.

01:05:00.189 --> 01:05:03.545
In your twenties, all you needed
was the two of you being adorable...

01:05:03.545 --> 01:05:05.046
Unbelievable.

01:05:05.046 --> 01:05:06.891
It's bugging me.

01:05:06.891 --> 01:05:08.716
Unless you're faking your reading
just to steal glances at me,

01:05:08.716 --> 01:05:10.086
how come you haven't gotten past
the first page?

01:05:10.086 --> 01:05:13.433
Your mother wants to know
if you and Ui Yeong are working out.

01:05:14.593 --> 01:05:17.206
When that story runs,
everyone's going to start asking about you.

01:05:17.206 --> 01:05:19.394
Reporters will come looking for you everywhere.

01:05:19.394 --> 01:05:20.506
Go study abroad.

01:05:20.506 --> 01:05:22.184
I don't know much,

01:05:22.184 --> 01:05:25.226
but I hope you hold on to what you love.

01:05:25.226 --> 01:05:27.235
I want to try

01:05:27.235 --> 01:05:29.449
being in love with you.